@PREV "requirements"
@NEXT "howtouse"

@{u}@{b}Installation@{ub}@{uu}

Best use the present installer-script.

If you want, you can also install BloodBath by yourself.
Copy all files into one drawer and change the icons-set to "standard" if you
don't use MagicWorkBench.
You must have a "bb:" assign to the drawer also.

@ENDNODE


@NODE "howtouse" "How to use"
@PREV "install"
@NEXT "testsamples"

@{b}@{u}Usage@{ub}@{uu}

Using BloodBath is very easy. You can start it from the Workbench, by
a doubleclick on the BloodBath-icon. Or the intro-icon if you want to see
the intro-anim.

In the game you press the button "start" and now you are playning!

And the question all asked...

